<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871218-0149 </DOCNO><HL> Dividend News:Tidewater Inc.</HL><DD> 12/18/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TDWDIVIDENDS (DIV) </IN><TEXT>   TIDEWATER INC. said it reached agreements with its primary lenders, Manufacturers Hanover Trust Co. and Prudential Insurance Co. of America, allowing it to pay dividends on its convertible adjustable preferred stock, series 494. Dividend payments on the preferred as well as on the New Orleans-based offshore service vessel company's common stock were suspended in October 1986 as part of a loan agreement. Tidewater said the new agreement allows it to pay, at its discretion, five dividends on the preferred through 1989. The first dividend, of $1.50 a share, is payable Feb. 1 to stock of record Dec. 31. Dividend payments on the common, most recently paid at a rate of five cents a share on April 16, 1986, remain suspended. </TEXT></DOC>